TANZANIA Wheelchair Basketball Association (TWBA) is still looking for 15m/- to send both men and women teams at the forthcoming East African Zone V Wheelchair Basketball Championship. The zonal competition is scheduled to be held from October 17-20th this year in Nairobi, Kenya. Ahead of the event, Tanzania Basketball Federation (TBF) has called on support from the government, public and private institutions as well as individual towards wheelchair men and women teams. TBF president Phares Magesa said that TWBA and teams are working hard to prepare for the same and they real need support for the dream competition. “We are calling for support toward our teams, they are looking for 15m/-, to facilitate their preparation and participation in the championship,” he said. TWBA Technical Director Azizy Mtogole said that Tanzania is looking forward for a maiden appearance in the competition. “We have received invitation to take part at the event and it is an opportunity for us to demonstrate what we are doing towards development of the game in Tanzania. We really need support to be able to travel to Nairobi,” he said. Mtogole said the 15m/- will cover transport, food and accommodation and other team expenses for 25 players and officials during the event. He said that Tanzania has strong and talented players who are able to compete against other top players at the international stage, but will need support to fulfill that. Mtogole said both teams are gearing up to showcase their skills at the event with their sight set on winning the titles. He said so far they have received about 1.7m/- from Sanitas Hospital through Dr Omaga Edward and other individuals. Tanzania will have to do it against other top teams including their East African Community (EAC) rivals Uganda, Rwanda and hosts Kenya.